Poor communication through digital platforms can easily lead to misunderstandings. For example, if a student sends an email to a professor without a subject line, greeting, or basic politeness, it might seem rude or unprofessional. Because of this, the professor may ignore the email or not take it seriously.

This can be avoided by following simple email etiquette. It’s also a good idea to read your message before sending it to make sure everything is clear and appropriate. Doing this helps create a good impression and makes it more likely that your message will be taken seriously.
